The macOS installer for 3.11.1 has been updated, so now when the application runs it does so in &ldquo;light theme mode&rdquo; (the Aqua look) on macOS Mojave. &#x1f604;
https://download.sqlitebrowser.org/DB.Browser.for.SQLite-3.11.1v2.dmg
It&rsquo;s a workaround for anyone using Mojave in Dark mode, which Qt doesn&rsquo;t yet properly support. Without this workaround, the colour pallete was unusable in important places. eg white on white when browsing data &#x1f626;
Jesse Jackson, thank you so much for showing us how to fix this problem.
